6.  The contract includes the following indicative deliverables: 
(i)  inception, midterm, and final reports as part of an overall work-flow process; 
(ii)  electronic document management system for online submission of regulatory 
returns and disclosures; 
(iii)  operation manuals and training materials; and 
(iv)  testing of software before SISB deployment. 

C.  National Consultant (8 person-months) 

7.  Insurance  industry  specialist  (8  person-months).  The  specialist  should  preferably 
have a master’s degree in economics, finance, or a related discipline, and at least 7 years of 
professional experience in the respective field of expertise. The specialist should have extensive 
working experience in the insurance market in Uzbekistan and sufficient knowledge of relevant 
stakeholders in the market. The specialist should have good organizational and networking 
skills. The specialist will: 
(i)  work closely with the team leader and other members of the team to implement 
TA activities; 
(ii)  provide  local  context  to  the  project,  in  particular  for  the  insurance  industry 
assessment; 
(iii)  collect data and information and undertake research as required; 
(iv)  manage meeting schedules for country visits; 
(v)  assist in organizing training and workshops; 
(vi)  participate in team discussions and contribute to recommendations; and 
(vii)  provide inputs to reports prepared under the TA.
